290 HORACE, ODES 111. xii—xiv.

Metre. A stanza consisting of ten feet called Ionici a minore. Each foot is of the form νν--. The last syllable cannot be doubtful, but must be long even at the end of the stanza. The lines have been arranged in various ways, to suit the convenience of the copyist or the printer. (Obs. the ionicus a maiore begins with the long syllables, thus, --νν.)
